      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements for the FDA generic pump geometry across 5 flow-speed operating points. All predicted RH values below 1.0 acceptance criterion. Inherent variability in blood sample haematocrit, erythrocyte fragility, and inter-donor biological variability was assessed qualitatively by the modelling team; no structured uncertainty propagation or probabilistic bounding was performed for this result, as the team judged the biological scatter to be within acceptable engineering tolerances based on prior literature review."
    }
